data.description: *Price dropped due to changes in health and circumstances. Good home with land for a great price in a fantastic location. Solid house with many upgrades.   Imagine owning a 1.37 surveyed acre Homestead where you can grown your own food. Get that country feel but enjoy all the convinces and shopping within 2 miles of your new home.   You can have some great get togethers and gather around the large backyard fire pit. There's plenty of space to run in your huge yard and play on the large playground. But if that's not enough, Adventure park is just up the road with a wonderful playground and a 1 mile paved walking and fitness trail.   This Open concept raised ranch with a walk out basement has plenty of space. With a few updates to the downstairs kitchen there is even plenty of room for a mother-in-law suite.    There are many perks to owning this home...  Hampden Township = lowest taxes around!  1 attached 2 car garage. 1 detached 2car garage or workshop. Bonus room downstairs currently being used as an in-home theater with raised seating. Could be 4th bedroom (unconventional) or a man cave!   Finished family room downstairs for more living space. Large storage room downstairs with lots of shelves to organize all your belongings.  Another storage room under the sunroom with outside access is a great place for your outdoor toys, an animal shelter, barn, or brooder house for baby chicks. Wood burning forced air furnace. Can also use coal and oil. (Oil tank for the furnace is not hooked up and the new owner would need to have it serviced before hooking it up.) We always use wood but coal is great for night time longer burn times and more economical. This unit is as easy as building a camp fire.  Firewood Wood storage under the deck conveniently located right outside the storage room door. Functional wood burning fireplace between the open living room and dining room. New furnace blower installed January 2023. Many kitchen and Bath updates to include new flooring, New sinks, faucets, toilet, showerheads and updated plumbing.  Well water - Well installed Oct 2011. Septic installed Oct 2011 and was pumped and inspected in June 2023 by Dillsburg septic. Septic is a sandmound with 1500 gal tanks and a pump. New electrical meter box and electric lines professionally installed August 2019. Many new outlets installed July 2023. Water pressure tank installed 2011. 200 gallon Hot water heater installed 2020 Roof in tact and does not leak.   ***The swimming pool was damaged from a tree falling in it during a storm. It has not been used for many years and will not be repaired by the seller.***
